> <span class="custom-chapter-break__hed">A New Life, in Limbo</span></h3></div><div data-fixed-bg-stack="cb2" class="fixed-bg-item fixed-bg-item--text" data-fx="hide"><h3 class="custom-chapter-break__text | size12 center"><span class="custom-chapter-break__kicker">Chapter Two</span> <span class="custom-chapter-break__hed">Elayna Comes Home</span></h3></div><div data-fixed-bg-stack="cb3" class="fixed-bg-item fixed-bg-item--text" data-fx="hide"><h3 class="custom-chapter-break__text | size12 center"><span class="custom-chapter-break__kicker">Chapter Three</span> <span class="custom-chapter-break__hed">Gravitational Pulls</span></h3></div><div data-fixed-bg-stack="cb4" class="fixed-bg-item fixed-bg-item--text" data-fx="hide"><h3 class="custom-chapter-break__text | size12 center"><span class="custom-chapter-break__kicker">Chapter Four</span> <span class="custom-chapter-break__hed">A Family on the Edge</span></h3></div><img data-fixed-bg-stack="99" class="fixed-bg-item fixed-bg-item--image" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0nMTYwMCcgaGVpZ2h0PSc5MDAnIHZpZXdCb3g9JzAgMCAxNjAwIDkwMCcgZmlsbD0nbm9uZScgeG1sbnM9J2h0dHA6Ly93d3cudzMub3JnLzIwMDAvc3ZnJz48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0nMTYwMCcgaGVpZ2h0PSc5MDAnIGZpbGw9J2JsYWNrJy8+PC9zdmc+Cg==" data-fx="hide"></div><section class="section-intro"><div class="scrolly"><div class="size08 center"><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--75" data-step-fx-hide="1"><div class="fade--text"><p class="text-style-copy--lg">When she got pregnant, Mayron Michelle Hollis was clinging to stability.</p></div></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" data-step-fx-show="1" style=""></div><div class="size06 left out03 wide-md"><div class="scrolly__step" data-step-fx-show="1"><p class="caption-bg">At 31, she was three years sober, after first getting introduced to drugs at 12. She had just had a baby three months earlier and was working to repair the damage that her addiction had caused her family.</p></div></div><div class="size06 left out03 wide-md"><div class="scrolly__step" data-step-fx-show="1"><p class="caption-bg">The state of Tennessee had taken away three of her children, and she was fighting to keep her infant daughter, Zooey. Department of Children’s Services investigators had accused Mayron of endangering Zooey when she visited a vape store and left the baby in a car.</p></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--75"><div class="stack stack--row stack--spacing-gutter stack--align-center stack--collapse-below-lg stack--column-reverse-below-lg"><div class="stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size06 left out03 wide-md"><p>Her husband, Chris Hollis, was also in recovery.</p><p>The two worked in physically demanding jobs that paid just enough to cover rent, food and lawyers’ fees to fight the state for custody of Mayron’s children.</p><p>In the midst of the turmoil in July 2022, they learned Mayron was pregnant again. But this time, doctors warned she and her fetus might not survive.</p></div><div class="stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size07 right out03 wide-md"><img style="margin-bottom: 0;" class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-hug-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=71bd63044b0b0afa4c314c2922d48684" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-hug-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=699b033d5af955410739e363f0eab380 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-hug-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=71bd63044b0b0afa4c314c2922d48684 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-hug-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=8b303f040e8fc8044f57d493c7a07150 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-hug-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=d4f5aba8919dd0ca76549c10726125d3 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-hug-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=720ebadd8e16893db5147cf1eb9b87b9 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-hug-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=345108fdb66835d804c3fa369383867e 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-hug-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=c2a9b06d82e243251770026abd3ef15a 2000w"></div></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--sticky scrolly__step--150"><div class="stack stack--row-reverse stack--spacing-gutter stack--align-start stack--collapse-below-lg"><div class="sticky-element | stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col | stack--spacing1 | size05 right out02 wide-md"><div><img class="" alt="" width="2142" height="3000" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-scar-portrait-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1120&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=041ebd2547e2ad65c705e2147eb987ee" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-scar-portrait-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=560&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=6fff60a6253bf47fd02032d3e84fb566 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-scar-portrait-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1120&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=041ebd2547e2ad65c705e2147eb987ee 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-scar-portrait-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1681&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=40498bf65a3bc7810de9c76511e46702 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-scar-portrait-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1821&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=635cc68b9f1b6cda1faf0d62898eaa4d 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-scar-portrait-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=2031&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=2a2cbb26c83fdf52bec79fb0fd18807a 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-scar-portrait-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=2241&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=31fce032d2f727ff628d9c60a8b02e38 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-intro-scar-portrait-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=2801&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=63008cea480b5e2d7ec3d79dc299f7ad 2000w"><figcaption class="attribution"><span class="attribution__caption">After Mayron Hollis’ pregnancy became life-threatening, doctors had to make a vertical incision to deliver her baby and remove her uterus.</span></figcaption></div></div><div class="stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size06 left out03 wide-md"><p>The embryo had been implanted in scar tissue from her recent cesarean section. There was a high chance that the embryo could rupture, blowing open her uterus and killing her, or that she could bleed to death during delivery. The baby could come months early and face serious medical risks, or even die.</p><p>But the Supreme Court had just overturned Roe v. Wade, which guaranteed the right to abortion across the United States. By the time Mayron decided to end her pregnancy, Tennessee’s abortion ban — one of the nation’s strictest — had gone into effect.</p><p>The total ban made no explicit exceptions — not even to save the life of a pregnant patient. Any doctor who violated the ban could be charged with a felony.</p><p>Women with means could leave the state. But those like Mayron, with limited resources or lives entangled with the child welfare and criminal justice systems, would be the most likely to face caring for a child they weren’t prepared for.</p></div></div></div><div class="size08 center"><div class="scrolly__step"><p>And so, the same state that questioned Mayron’s fitness to care for her four children <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.propublica.org/article/tennessee-abortion-ban-doctors-ectopic-pregnancy&sa=D&source=docs&ust=1707875360075336&usg=AOvVaw3uDY_PS9tnLoT4dn5gvYrE">forced her to continue a pregnancy that risked her life</a> to have a fifth, one that would require more intensive care than any of the others.</p><p>Tennessee already had some of the worst outcomes in the nation when measuring maternal health, infant mortality and child poverty. Lawmakers who paved the way for a new generation of post-Roe births did little to bolster the state’s meager safety net to support these babies and their families.</p><p>In December 2022, when Mayron was 26 weeks and two days pregnant, she was rushed to the hospital after she began bleeding so heavily that her husband slipped in her blood. An emergency surgery saved her life. Her daughter, Elayna, was born three months early.</p><p>Afterward, photographer Stacy Kranitz and reporter Kavitha Surana followed Mayron and her family for a year to chronicle what life truly looked like in a state whose political leaders say they are pro-life.</p></div></div></div></section><section class="section-chapter-1"><div class="scrolly"><div class="custom-chapter-break | scrolly__step scrolly__step--100" data-step-fx-show="cb1" data-step-fx-before-bg="1" data-step-fx-after-bg="2"></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" data-step-fx-show="2" style=""></div><div class="size06 left out03 wide-md"><div class="scrolly__step" data-step-fx-show="2"><p class="caption-bg">Born weighing less than 2 pounds and unable to breathe on her own, Elayna would need months in the neonatal intensive care unit. Her stay came with an estimated six-figure bill and was covered by the state-managed Medicaid program.</p></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only hide-on-desktop scrolly__step--75" style=""></div><div class="size08 center"><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--50"><div class="fade--text"><p class="text-style-copy--lg">On Dec. 21, days after Mayron was discharged from the hospital, she was arrested.</p></div></div></div><div class="scrolly__step"><div class="stack stack--row stack--spacing-gutter stack--align-center stack--collapse-below-lg"><div class="stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size06 left out01 wide-md"><p>She had thought the case related to leaving her daughter in the car was resolved when state child welfare officials closed the matter. But prosecutors had separately filed a felony criminal charge. The penalty is eight to 30 years in prison.</p><p>She paid a $6,000 bond to be released from jail and found a lawyer willing to represent her for a $6,000 fee by payment plan.</p></div><div class="stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size03 right out01 wide-md"><div><img src="https://assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20240108-Mayron-PE-1-mugshot.jpg"><figcaption class="attribution"><span class="attribution__caption">Montgomery County Sheriff’s Office</span></figcaption></div></div></div></div><div class="size10 center"><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--75"><div class="fade--text"><p class="text-style-copy--lg">The arrest had depleted any savings she and Chris had put aside to take off work for Elayna’s first weeks. Now they were in debt.</p></div></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--150"><div class="stack stack--row stack--spacing-gutter stack--align-start stack--collapse-below-lg"><div class="sticky-element | stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size06 out03 left wide-md"><p>Mayron, who was still recovering from a lifesaving surgery that removed her uterus, returned to work as an insulator apprentice two weeks later.</p><p>Her husband, Chris, also had to work. Neither of them had paid parental leave.</p></div><div class="stack stack--col stack__item-no-shrink | stack--spacing1 | right size05 out02 wide-md"><img class="" alt="" width="2142" height="3000" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-flag-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1120&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=d4f9fb4cb3b059dd47a0fd72c85bc5cd" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-flag-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=560&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=5103903e2081adcc6a07c995e1e58973 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-flag-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1120&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=d4f9fb4cb3b059dd47a0fd72c85bc5cd 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-flag-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1681&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=b0ea805dab0090a0376cc4db113afcbb 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-flag-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1821&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=b61c15681fc0b56df99f0e036ea79ced 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-flag-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=2031&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=17c68eeb08d9952edf5c64f158e6cafb 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-flag-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=2241&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=0f3cda695adc2da7a238d94aa5647c73 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-flag-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=2801&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=0c06ce50c7315174960f5128c4a0eb75 2000w"><div><img class="" alt="" width="2142" height="3000" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-notebook-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1120&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=0a8c7c12c1b19bad3c7306e30919bdc0" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-notebook-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=560&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=34d3067c2bb0b551897aa5a4616121fd 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-notebook-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1120&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=0a8c7c12c1b19bad3c7306e30919bdc0 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-notebook-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1681&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=b93035a37f8a7cda705482e6684e3075 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-notebook-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1821&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=b5ad766b6a924f0b2b02a058496a9153 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-notebook-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=2031&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=807cc6c04305428174e995c455023ec8 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-notebook-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=2241&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=50f160c187ecb163ff81b0bd86f3a8d8 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230121-mayron-pe-1-work-notebook-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=2801&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=a2ad3360b44c2cfa4c9df7551b4aabb3 2000w"><figcaption class="attribution"><span class="attribution__caption">During her breaks at work, Mayron called the hospital from her car to check on Elayna’s progress, jotting down notes.</span></figcaption></div></div></div></div><div class="size08 center"><div class="account-aside | scrolly__step" data-step-fx-fade="3"><div class="account-aside__box"><h3 class="account-aside__hed"><span class="account-aside__hed-kicker">Safety Net</span> <span class="account-aside__hed-main">Parental Leave</span></h3><p><a href="https://www.kff.org/womens-health-policy/fact-sheet/paid-leave-in-u-s/">Research</a> indicates access to paid family leave is linked to a decrease in infant deaths and better economic, physical and mental health for new parents.</p><p>Currently, <a href="https://www.americanprogress.org/article/the-state-of-paid-family-and-medical-leave-in-the-u-s-in-2023/#:~:text=Eleven%20states%20have%20passed%20paid,24%20along%20with%20Washington%2C%20D.C">13 states</a> have some form of paid parental leave to care for newborns.</p><p>No states that banned abortion offer paid parental leave.</p></div></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" data-step-fx-show="3" style=""></div><div class="size06 right out03 wide-md"><div class="scrolly__step" data-step-fx-show="3"><p class="caption-bg">There were no facilities equipped to handle Elayna’s needs in their county.</p></div></div><div class="size06 right out03 wide-md"><div class="scrolly__step" data-step-fx-show="3"><p class="caption-bg">So Elayna spent many of her earliest moments without her parents, in a hospital an hour away.</p></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--75" data-step-fx-hide="3"><div class="stack stack--row stack--spacing-gutter stack--align-center stack--collapse-below-lg"><div class="stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size06 left out03 wide-md"><p>Charities offer free housing near the hospital for parents of some children in the NICU. Mayron called nearly every day after her daughter was born, but none had any openings for weeks.</p><p>After her 10-hour shifts, Mayron visited Elayna as often as she could, sometimes sleeping in her car in the hospital’s parking garage.</p></div><div class="stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size07 right out03 wide-md"><img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-1-sleeping-car-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=5aec1939c7187e0fab3cfaea13369066" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-1-sleeping-car-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=6bd1c0f9193ccba8106b09bc1341f010 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-1-sleeping-car-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=5aec1939c7187e0fab3cfaea13369066 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-1-sleeping-car-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=d4b1779fc2eafa44560d747dcfb1f4e9 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-1-sleeping-car-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=b3e828414007d80110235980f83aee61 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-1-sleeping-car-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=88e0461d29b03c25763b41bf8076777d 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-1-sleeping-car-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=cdb03c6f7de83cc9d0504b3c9ed3f17c 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-1-sleeping-car-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=b41fc2cdb7605347035d4af398206ea3 2000w"></div></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only" data-step-fx-show="4" style=""></div><div class="size08 center"><div class="scrolly__step"><p>While Elayna remained in the hospital, the family was eligible for disability payments from the federal government for having a child born weighing less than 2 pounds. They amounted to $30 a month.</p><p>Mayron wasn’t sure how to access them — but they wouldn’t even cover a week of gas money to and from the hospital anyway.</p></div></div></div></section><section class="section-chapter-2"><div class="scrolly"><div class="custom-chapter-break | scrolly__step" data-step-fx-show="cb2" data-step-fx-before-bg="2" data-step-fx-after-bg="3"></div><div class="size08 center"><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--50"><div class="fade--text"><p class="text-style-copy--lg">Mayron brought Elayna home in late February, on her daughter Zooey’s first birthday.</p></div></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only" data-step-fx-show="5" style="margin-top: 0; height: 100vh;"></div><div class="size08 center"><div class="scrolly__step"><p>But Elayna’s health was still fragile. Twice in the first month she was rushed back to the hospital because of lung infections.</p></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only" data-step-fx-show="6" style="margin-top: 0; height: 100vh;"></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step"><img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230428-mayron-pe-2-feeding-tube-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=98e3c4236ba17dfba72c08b9e9c09061" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230428-mayron-pe-2-feeding-tube-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=78edbefc6841fb824ef64abd72ca11d0 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230428-mayron-pe-2-feeding-tube-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=98e3c4236ba17dfba72c08b9e9c09061 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230428-mayron-pe-2-feeding-tube-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=aba6e99542512670e7bfdd9a3ba6d0d6 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230428-mayron-pe-2-feeding-tube-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=b1d1f6fb25bb4a5404ff71d8beeed85f 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230428-mayron-pe-2-feeding-tube-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=e3d44b5b58b3cdb0f19d5dcd45d71d03 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230428-mayron-pe-2-feeding-tube-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=41b154bb4c320f4fdec2831ba2ec8eac 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230428-mayron-pe-2-feeding-tube-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=0e2df3d95669591eb9a34eba7956e816 2000w"><p>Once home, her medical needs were complex. She had a feeding tube, breathed with the help of a machine and needed to see a pediatrician, an eye doctor, a lung specialist and an occupational therapist.</p></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only hide-on-desktop" style="margin-top:-90vh"></div><div class="scrolly__step"><img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-mayron-both-babies-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=ca49af6aa61516591de0c8f75217b576" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-mayron-both-babies-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=f3d601c36a0998e72c6f2c389ecd1813 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-mayron-both-babies-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=ca49af6aa61516591de0c8f75217b576 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-mayron-both-babies-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=2e95dcffaeb0cd2e533172c92567cd85 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-mayron-both-babies-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=82d37b094779e5bc33a0214ff0fb285a 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-mayron-both-babies-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=39d67c7cc6540139fb067177b8656a81 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-mayron-both-babies-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=2bd6e9b4bb937d094c5e312b801fc8ac 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-mayron-both-babies-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=c1fb0ef83060d42c86d83587dcec708d 2000w"><p>Mayron quit her job to navigate Elayna’s care.</p></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--sticky scrolly__step--200"><div class="stack stack--row-reverse stack--spacing-gutter stack--align-start stack--collapse-below-lg"><div class="sticky-element | stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col | stack--spacing1 | size07 right out03 wide-md"><img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230120-mayron-pe-2-paperwork-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=2194cf39d209ab0c99d7fd4261579ff6" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230120-mayron-pe-2-paperwork-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=e3719445a58b05315fb5c4cdd0c55610 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230120-mayron-pe-2-paperwork-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=2194cf39d209ab0c99d7fd4261579ff6 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230120-mayron-pe-2-paperwork-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=0927c979d7e3e6de9fdb8b242cf6d099 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230120-mayron-pe-2-paperwork-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=da9b88e64f27550f07c2563e3f23566b 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230120-mayron-pe-2-paperwork-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=ecd6676386293bf48604aa77f90faf98 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230120-mayron-pe-2-paperwork-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=4e7ec1776acc6acae936b1b9dadf51c1 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230120-mayron-pe-2-paperwork-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=8da94ff954bbe310ae2970693ae6bae7 2000w"></div><div class="stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size06 left out03 wide-md"><p>Donations to Mayron’s GoFundMe after ProPublica wrote about her story helped the family keep up with rent, lawyer and court fees, debt, gas and baby supplies for a few months.</p><p>Mayron filled out paperwork to get help to pay for her daughter’s needs. She knew Elayna should have been eligible for disability support, given her premature birth and developmental challenges. But none of the phone calls she made or forms she submitted seemed to lead to any aid. It would be almost a year before Mayron received a letter that said Social Security approved $914 per month in disability payments for Elayna. It retroactively covered February to August but was cut off after that with no explanation. The family has never received any of the money.</p><p>Mayron knew she was supposed to qualify for at-home help from a nurse while Elayna was on the feeding tube, and she asked the hospital for assistance setting it up when she was going home. But she ran into issues getting her insurance to approve it. In the end, it was too late: A nurse finally showed up for a visit two days after Elayna was already taken off the feeding tube.</p><p>Mayron decided not to apply for unemployment. She didn’t understand the rules and felt it would be too risky. She had applied for unemployment while she had to take leave for her high-risk pregnancy with Elayna, but a mistake on the paperwork later meant she had to pay back some of the money with fees. She also didn’t qualify for disability support because her complications from the surgery were considered short-term and partial.</p></div></div></div><div class="size08 center"><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--50"><div class="fade--text"><p class="text-style-copy--lg">The new financial needs were crushing.</p></div></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only" data-step-fx-show="7" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step"><div class="stack stack--row stack--spacing-gutter stack--align-start stack--collapse-below-lg"><div class="sticky-element | stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size06 left out03 wide-md"><p>By late spring, Mayron and Chris’ bank account balance was dwindling to the hundreds. They began to fall behind on their $1,400 monthly rent and $550 car payments.</p><p>Their cars kept breaking down. Chris needed a reliable truck for the business he runs installing vinyl siding. They saw a special offer for financing, so they went to a dealership to see if they could get a new one. They had been using a $400 credit card to build up credit and Mayron’s score was above 700, but their history was too short and they didn’t qualify for a loan.</p><p>More credit card offers kept arriving in their mailbox. The couple applied for them and other loans and bought used cars at double-digit interest rates so they could get to work.</p></div><div class="stack stack--col stack__item-no-shrink | stack--spacing1 | size07 right out03 wide-md"><img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-2-walmart-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=c7d4315186799a2d098fe8fbfb4955b6" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-2-walmart-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=b711db792ffabae4812c46ec7f16f8a4 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-2-walmart-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=c7d4315186799a2d098fe8fbfb4955b6 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-2-walmart-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=a4d837187e2334a435bc4fc504bed1d2 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-2-walmart-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=3ce0226e1a38f9bca006947993fb5880 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-2-walmart-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=29687bdeba37fc0c663257b70191e160 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-2-walmart-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=60bd9cbba8f5e9faea5d686486dd09bd 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20221218-mayron-pe-2-walmart-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=08d1ce4c680262e796096ad5a510f44c 2000w"> <img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230219-mayron-pe-2-chris-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=f108ed5a760506d7d805873adfa21668" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230219-mayron-pe-2-chris-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=e029e68a373300494bf8ea95601a102e 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230219-mayron-pe-2-chris-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=f108ed5a760506d7d805873adfa21668 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230219-mayron-pe-2-chris-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=2491a3b0d205b421df792766ab2fd83c 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230219-mayron-pe-2-chris-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=353638f540ed6ac8185e16d32078c4ab 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230219-mayron-pe-2-chris-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=e7bcfb54aecd9546256222635463924b 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230219-mayron-pe-2-chris-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=025b04332316490a282d1b38ac660fec 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230219-mayron-pe-2-chris-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=bfa1370135421fa259692b5e0866930c 2000w"> <img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-car-dealership-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=e5a5217466c63c34f7398d4eded19474" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-car-dealership-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=4436221ee47156517939a804e3db9253 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-car-dealership-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=e5a5217466c63c34f7398d4eded19474 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-car-dealership-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=6c5964e26a4decabac65d65ff874b1e6 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-car-dealership-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=7abc4a6b13ab9c14e8bd0e23642bc1c4 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-car-dealership-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=01fa4be9d4ee18da85c3fc810cbee42e 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-car-dealership-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=19c7a51f88c14dd18309827a9f893aaa 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-car-dealership-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=d8238f0e3fe824e6362ee1d317a0fece 2000w"></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="scrolly__step"><p>After Elayna came off the feeding tube in May, they decided Mayron needed to go back to work. She could make about $600 a week installing insulation. But first they had to figure out child care. Elayna was still too fragile for full-time day care. According to care.com, an experienced nanny in their city would cost about the same as Mayron’s weekly paycheck.</p><p>On Facebook, they found a 24-year-old babysitter who charged $250 a week to watch the two girls.</p></div></div><div class="size08 center"><div class="account-aside | scrolly__step" data-step-fx-fade="8"><div class="account-aside__box"><h3 class="account-aside__hed"><span class="account-aside__hed-kicker">Safety Net</span> <span class="account-aside__hed-main">Child Care</span></h3><p>In 2019, nearly half of Tennesseans lived in a <a href="https://tqee.org/child-care-study/#:~:text=Two%2Dthirds%20of%20parents%20said,care%20is%20a%20big%20challenge">child care desert</a>, an area that has three times as many children as licensed child care slots. In Mayron’s city, Clarksville, more than 3,000 children in 2023 qualified for <a href="https://myutk.maps.arcgis.com/apps/instant/interactivelegend/index.html?appid=faf30217675f4df9842de4c6ea02b9f3">government assistance for child care</a>, but 941 were unable to access it.</p><p>Between 2011 and 2020, 13 bills aimed at alleviating child care burdens were <a href="https://www.healthyandfreetn.org/tennessee_over_ten_report">proposed</a> in the Tennessee legislature. All of them failed.</p></div></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" data-step-fx-show="8" style=""></div><div class="size06 right out03 wide-md"><div class="scrolly__step" data-step-fx-show="8"><p class="caption-bg">Mayron would leave for work at 4:45 a.m.</p></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step"><img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-morning-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=0746174fcd7a7e1c808304bcbf040e5e" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-morning-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=f713aef454ff09f49168c9744d418a4a 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-morning-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=0746174fcd7a7e1c808304bcbf040e5e 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-morning-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=f7a9c018eb757d1d89f702b4ce578a22 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-morning-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=eb32f2c16e6f551d389e6c98c3e19579 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-morning-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=20520fea48b0cfa4f4f0bcffd7c7f879 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-morning-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=34c90443b85322f06b3f280dff3595ec 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-morning-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=225a5f8bc58fea1e99366c57bf40c42d 2000w"><p>Chris would watch the girls until the babysitter arrived, around 7 a.m. Then, he headed to work too.</p></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only hide-on-desktop" style="margin-top:-90vh"></div><div class="scrolly__step"><figure><img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-shower-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=ac69930c51a55b1f9f6abf855b76ceb7" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-shower-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=4f4fe85a8c22dd76707766264a82c2e4 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-shower-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=ac69930c51a55b1f9f6abf855b76ceb7 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-shower-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=d95d5027576d485d25277c5d2cb2f7c3 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-shower-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=f396e3cb154f014980838ad48db8a0cd 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-shower-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=33c0ea38dc55756bf3cbff975c1d1900 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-shower-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=67670fcd6fc6447d88d55e0c00576e07 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-shower-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=01fd13eda9f5b97e8ecbde66b12377f9 2000w"><figcaption class="attribution"><span class="attribution__caption">Mayron eats dinner while bathing Zooey after work.</span></figcaption></figure><p>Mayron returned every night after 5 p.m., often covered in fiberglass, then launched into cleaning the house and the evening routine with her girls.</p></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only hide-on-desktop" style="margin-top:-80vh"></div><div class="scrolly__step"><figure><img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-physical-therapy-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=26dac338bc13129f5485798bd8121e3b" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-physical-therapy-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=ec4655e8b53d27bd59a310a2857319a0 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-physical-therapy-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=26dac338bc13129f5485798bd8121e3b 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-physical-therapy-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=70ec2c9a79d35ab91d460ffca05fa11c 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-physical-therapy-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=7c6be2c80ca3183068827f1d5f7562e5 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-physical-therapy-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=f54f51f716be914dc53ec97aa82a9093 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-physical-therapy-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=1064a272a7454681176e60f7f3082832 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230624-mayron-pe-2-physical-therapy-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=52befb326e53291e0c2b051c071ef342 2000w"><figcaption class="attribution"><span class="attribution__caption">Mayron does physical therapy with Elayna.</span></figcaption></figure><p>After four months, Mayron got connected with an early intervention program that could provide free virtual therapy to support Elayna’s movement and development.</p></div><div class="size08 center"><div class="account-aside | scrolly__step" data-step-fx-fade="9"><div class="account-aside__box"><h3 class="account-aside__hed"><span class="account-aside__hed-kicker">Safety Net</span> <span class="account-aside__hed-main">Early Intervention</span></h3><p>Children born preterm are at risk for developmental delays and disabilities, and all states have free or reduced-cost programs to provide support. Yet researchers <a href="https://pn3policy.org/pn-3-state-policy-roadmap-2022/us/early-intervention/">say</a> not enough low-income families are able to access those programs. Many states don’t actively connect children with these services because their programs aren’t well-funded, they say.</p><p>In Tennessee, less than 3% of eligible children in low-income families <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://pn3policy.org/pn-3-state-policy-roadmap-2022/us/home-visiting/&sa=D&source=docs&ust=1707876519186517&usg=AOvVaw3WFvuErrQPN8cYYM9Uqo8a">are enrolled</a> in evidence-based home visiting programs, one of the lowest rates in the country.</p></div></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only" data-step-fx-show="9" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--200"><div class="stack stack--row stack--spacing-gutter stack--align-start stack--collapse-below-lg stack--column-reverse-below-lg"><div class="sticky-element | stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size06 left out03 wide-md"><p>By summer, Elayna was getting stronger each day and Zooey was getting into everything.</p><p>Mayron and Chris started dreaming of a house for their girls. One that didn’t have a rusted bathtub, mice infestations and heat that broke down in the winter. They also wanted to move away from neighbors who frequently overdosed, a stressful reminder of their past.</p></div><div class="stack stack--col stack__item-no-shrink | stack--spacing1 | size07 right out03 wide-md"><img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-slide-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=630cc4d7d04e0760258090c22c5df7d8" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-slide-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=20280247d57c0a81a1696c63273103c7 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-slide-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=630cc4d7d04e0760258090c22c5df7d8 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-slide-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=ca5d2c894bf044ff01a16c5b98c02350 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-slide-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=a742706a4b5fd0e7006c6379feeed53b 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-slide-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=7740ce97d8e5a71450f1b5edc80dd073 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-slide-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=451653141d77881887e6ecf32efada8c 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230528-mayron-pe-2-chris-slide-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=3816edafb41e68dae6006a9f0bb8a58a 2000w"> <img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-zooey-crate-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=e66b4fd95610ecf56630bf8cb63f2032" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-zooey-crate-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=c90aef9dc64999852d2456a9591943cd 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-zooey-crate-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=e66b4fd95610ecf56630bf8cb63f2032 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-zooey-crate-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=5f7c81383dc59611afe53c39bfb25f0f 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230513-mayron-pe-2-zooey-crate-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp