p-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=009d84b9f26aeb35c4fdab64a84407ff 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/202309-mayron-pe-3-mayron-chris-fight-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=cba1c86fb7350f9d99514aeb4b9f5d34 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/202309-mayron-pe-3-mayron-chris-fight-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=2b85b73972093fe10394aa2851967d24 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/202309-mayron-pe-3-mayron-chris-fight-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=f7a25dec82f356c2c6d5ab98653c05fd 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/202309-mayron-pe-3-mayron-chris-fight-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=168dff5bc8d42c60c380a495c31870dc 2000w"></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only hide-on-desktop" style="margin-top:-75vh"></div><div class="size08 center"><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--75"><p>Mayron was struggling to cope with the pressure. She took medication to help with ADHD and suboxone for substance use disorder. In the past, she had tried some depression and anxiety medications prescribed by her doctors, but they made her feel sleepy and lethargic, so she didn’t continue. Other medications were off limits because of her addiction history.</p></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only" data-step-fx-show="14" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step"><figure><img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20220219-mayron-pe-3-certificate-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=a9f8138c6248c20afa666132ef455c6e" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20220219-mayron-pe-3-certificate-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=bdc2bb6ac6e3c637ed96a58fc84d0a1b 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20220219-mayron-pe-3-certificate-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=a9f8138c6248c20afa666132ef455c6e 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20220219-mayron-pe-3-certificate-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=a45d05cff8b370848ff73b1b125111df 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20220219-mayron-pe-3-certificate-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=dc32c911186f1e0bdb45d89ba7518a66 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20220219-mayron-pe-3-certificate-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=a1f6517fa7d1275e7ae836735af66a88 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20220219-mayron-pe-3-certificate-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=75cabb5e98ec80324c4d481d55d6b855 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20220219-mayron-pe-3-certificate-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=cd6a47084609aa6f1884a38eb9b3dac0 2000w"><figcaption class="attribution"><span class="attribution__caption">Mayron’s peer recovery specialist certificate bears her maiden name, York.</span></figcaption></figure><p>She had once hoped to find a job helping other mothers with substance use disorder, volunteering to lead Alcoholics Anonymous meetings and even earning a peer recovery specialist certificate while Elayna was in the hospital.</p></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only hide-on-desktop" style="margin-top:-100vh"></div><div class="scrolly__step"><img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230819-mayron-pe-3-crying-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=07a4de4d88de2c0e341a32603c005a15" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230819-mayron-pe-3-crying-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=9e834f9c3a5451bac96b70561e13dfeb 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230819-mayron-pe-3-crying-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=07a4de4d88de2c0e341a32603c005a15 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230819-mayron-pe-3-crying-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=a05c14d30d5759152ac9d0291158d15f 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230819-mayron-pe-3-crying-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=0bfc13082c023ba5fc499ad519a6486b 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230819-mayron-pe-3-crying-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=699b6faafc02c1a2901148ec1aed271c 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230819-mayron-pe-3-crying-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=ae8345f43d1fa3a24b2308e8e1b1fbfa 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230819-mayron-pe-3-crying-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=121454a09d5d27cf60fa84c9b3ba6c9d 2000w"><p>Now her own recovery was at risk.</p></div></div></section><section class="section-chapter-4"><div class="scrolly"><div class="custom-chapter-break | scrolly__step" data-step-fx-show="cb4" data-step-fx-before-bg="4" data-step-fx-after-bg="5"></div><div class="size10 center"><div class="scrolly__step"><div class="fade--text"><p class="text-style-copy--lg">Throughout the turmoil, Mayron and Chris had been able to keep a roof over their heads and put food on the table.</p><br><p class="text-style-copy--lg">By September, both were in peril.</p></div></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" data-step-fx-show="15" style=""></div><div class="size06 left out03 wide-md"><div class="scrolly__step" data-step-fx-show="15"><p class="caption-bg">Their landlord threatened eviction for late payments.</p></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step"><div class="stack stack--row stack--spacing-gutter stack--align-center stack--collapse-below-lg"><div class="stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size06 left out03 wide-md"><p>Their credit cards and loans were spiraling out of control. Besides paying off the cars for work, Chris sometimes used them to buy tools and to cover his workers’ salaries. Mayron used them to buy groceries and to make the house more comfortable. Soon they were nearly $40,000 in debt and their credit score had dropped about 200 points. Mayron was devastated when she finally realized the extent of it — there was no hope of achieving their dream to buy a house anytime soon, or even move.</p></div><div class="stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size07 right out03 wide-md"><img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-together-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=fcd2d3daadf14ed3f295ec55bd9bdc8f" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-together-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=f1c30881abc8ae1b8f26795348cdc889 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-together-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=fcd2d3daadf14ed3f295ec55bd9bdc8f 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-together-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=dd43a9e0b00b2d6a37f0cf156bdac23c 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-together-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=d0b04de0f87d8135328f70046d2f6dc6 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-together-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=10fcefe636e8b2de4d4c5b9650ce9ca3 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-together-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=95ba8c10fbdf0e8f04f344937c348c71 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-together-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=50daa613de16b6094c4bfa75fe720495 2000w"></div></div></div><div class="size08 center"><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--75"><p>They also learned they were losing their food stamps — $972 a month. Since Mayron went back to work, their income one month put them above the eligibility limit of $39,000 a year, before taxes, for a household of four.</p><p>Both their jobs were unpredictable, and the aid had been crucial to help them stay stocked with formula and baby food the past year.</p></div></div><div class="size08 center"><div class="account-aside | scrolly__step" data-step-fx-fade="16"><div class="account-aside__box"><h3 class="account-aside__hed"><span class="account-aside__hed-kicker">Safety Net</span> <span class="account-aside__hed-main">Government Assistance</span></h3><p>In Tennessee, a family of four making less than $39,000 a year should be eligible for food stamps if their current bank balance is under $3,001 and they share their household with a person over 60 or with a disability.</p><p>Tennessee’s child poverty rate ranks among the <a href="https://www.sycamoreinstitutetn.org/child-and-family-poverty-in-tennessee/">worst</a> in the nation, in part, because families who qualify for government help aren’t getting it. About 1 in 10 families eligible for food stamps <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://pn3policy.org/pn-3-state-policy-roadmap-2023/us/admin-burden/&sa=D&source=docs&ust=1707877125707318&usg=AOvVaw2j751eCnPHTi47hO2OIev6">aren’t receiving them</a>. According to researchers, the program requirements are too punitive and complicated, leaving such families shut out.</p><p>In 2019, the state was <a href="https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2023/03/27/what-happened-to-tennessees-732-million-for-families-in-need/70012181007/">holding</a> nearly $800 million in unspent federal funding designated for temporary assistance to needy families. Since then, monthly benefits for eligible Tennesseeans have barely risen, from $277 to $387 in 2021. That ranks among the lowest in the nation for temporary cash assistance.</p></div></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" data-step-fx-show="16" style=""></div><div class="size06 left out03 wide-md"><div class="scrolly__step" data-step-fx-show="16"><p class="caption-bg">In her lowest moments, Mayron felt she was failing her daughters. “I felt like: I’m not good enough to have them,” she said. “Like, I can’t afford them, because I can’t get them the things I want them to have.”</p></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--25" data-step-fx-show="16" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step"><div class="size14 center multi wide-md" style="margin-bottom: 1rem;"><img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-insulation-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=a76e58088cf14949c18ee72af5b6e6e5" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-insulation-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=21bee73e20d7298a66cec2aa559bdb84 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-insulation-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=a76e58088cf14949c18ee72af5b6e6e5 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-insulation-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=f8597edb777e53e6fe8956a3f2b85b90 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-insulation-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=65469aa10e192ccdabe6412e7ed55120 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-insulation-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=ed25c3ee094770805a5cfe3fce67d02a 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-insulation-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=4a319d231bd397e6048dfde84f2093a3 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-insulation-work-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=27dd35a6cb58529358d7909627b2da9f 2000w"> <img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-bar-eye-contact-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=6ac2a98c4ee543013e74261b84434502" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-bar-eye-contact-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=2480414f6bf55096dee9e5b3acc17e68 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-bar-eye-contact-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=6ac2a98c4ee543013e74261b84434502 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-bar-eye-contact-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=9858b9a3c6a01f042e5722c0fb5dee98 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-bar-eye-contact-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=0d4bf1348f962fde194b23c901e89efc 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-bar-eye-contact-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=d36e2c0376237b87052917cccddd3984 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-bar-eye-contact-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=15c22d3c0aaeb468b2c8506844f2c784 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-bar-eye-contact-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=959db8219881d0aaebeb6609035b22d2 2000w"></div><p>Mayron started meeting up with co-workers for drinks after work more often.</p><p>Then, Mayron’s temporary insulation gig finished and she was out of work. She would have to reapply for food stamps for the new year and wait months to see if they would be reinstated.</p></div><div class="size10 center"><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--75"><p class="fade--text text-style-copy--lg">As fall closed in, Mayron started having panic attacks and her health declined. She lost weight and barely slept.</p></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only" data-step-fx-show="17" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--sticky"><div class="stack stack--row-reverse stack--spacing-gutter stack--align-start stack--collapse-below-lg"><div class="sticky-element | stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col | stack--spacing1 | size05 right out02 wide-md"><img class="" alt="" width="2142" height="3000" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-overwhelmed-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1120&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=95d0d9e738e5025a91c2b82a25ce9f02" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-overwhelmed-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=560&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=5b8e4b45a4011792c6b6b4e998734e6d 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-overwhelmed-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1120&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=95d0d9e738e5025a91c2b82a25ce9f02 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-overwhelmed-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1681&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=70d129dc52ed805a2075ad0599e492e6 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-overwhelmed-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1821&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=31608cd3bfbce13f824d9d94ddaa0a09 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-overwhelmed-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=2031&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=7c29aa57f1181ce6696625be6528628d 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-overwhelmed-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=2241&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=7df2b60bc4fe6a79817ee9476ad77790 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-overwhelmed-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=2801&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=87ea8838650f39f07c8c2e024b7827e0 2000w"></div><div class="stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size06 left out03 wide-md"><p>Ever since her traumatic C-section, she noticed she no longer had any feeling when she went to the bathroom. Her stomach and back were sometimes numb or radiated pain. She knew doctors had removed her uterus, but she had never been totally clear about what had happened inside her body during the surgery or its long-term effects.</p><p>Mayron had state Medicaid insurance after Tennessee expanded coverage to women for one year after giving birth in 2022. But she was so consumed with holding things together, she never made time to see a doctor.</p><p>Mayron had a psychiatrist through a hospital research program for mothers in recovery for opioid addiction. When she could get an appointment, she talked with him about her ADHD medication over video calls, but she feared confiding in him about her stressors or the alcohol. She felt he would be too busy anyway.</p></div></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only hide-on-desktop" style="margin-top:-75vh"></div><div class="size08 center"><div class="scrolly__step"><p>Alcohol became a more frequent escape.</p><p>Sometimes it triggered her worst impulses.</p><p>Chris bore the brunt of her outbursts, especially over money.</p></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" data-step-fx-show="18" style=""></div><div class="size06 left out03 wide-md"><div class="scrolly__step" data-step-fx-show="18"><p class="caption-bg">Some days she raged from morning until night.</p></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step"><div class="stack stack--row stack--spacing-gutter stack--align-center stack--collapse-below-lg"><div class="stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size06 left out03 wide-md"><p>Chris had been dealing with his own mood swings and depression from not being able to provide for the family since Elayna’s birth. He usually kept quiet and retreated inside himself, but sometimes the stress broke through and he yelled back.</p><p>As the holidays approached, Mayron told Chris she wanted a separation.</p></div><div class="stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size07 right out03 wide-md"><img class="" alt="" width="3000" height="2142" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-porch-swing-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=9025001f74332872e2c8b75301011e3d" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-porch-swing-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=286&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=07a89899b676ef692bf7e1c1591869cc 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-porch-swing-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=571&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=9025001f74332872e2c8b75301011e3d 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-porch-swing-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=857&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=3b0706db946becdc65c5676b6511054a 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-porch-swing-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=928&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=8ae2bd8843521e18978aa3882e029a2e 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-porch-swing-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1035&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=0e878766cfddb8f761fa3a2b76b9cc02 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-porch-swing-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1142&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=3dd4f821f1b521b1476c5468fb2e00a5 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231119-mayron-pe-4-porch-swing-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1428&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=7f9ab6ddd12efb2ded7b979b6b9e3959 2000w"></div></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only hide-on-desktop" style="margin-top:-100vh"></div><div class="size08 center"><div class="scrolly__step"><p>Chris started to spiral. Two days before Thanksgiving, he relapsed.</p><p>The next week he checked into an inpatient mental health and rehab facility and stayed for a week.</p></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" data-step-fx-show="19" style=""></div><div class="size06 right out03 wide-md"><div class="scrolly__step" data-step-fx-show="19"><div class="caption-bg"><p>“This all broke me,” he wrote as his reason for admission, after recounting the events of the past year. “None of this is my fault but I’ve got to deal with it all. I try not to be resentful with my wife. I have trouble paying attention to my family, I space out.”</p></div></div></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--fx-only scrolly__step--50" style=""></div><div class="scrolly__step scrolly__step--200"><div class="stack stack--row stack--spacing-gutter stack--align-start stack--collapse-below-lg"><div class="sticky-element | stack__item-no-shrink | stack stack--col stack--spacing1 | size06 left out03 wide-md"><p>While Chris was in inpatient care, one of the neighbors offered to help Mayron around the house.</p><p>She started to spend more time with him.</p><p>By the end of the week, she had slept with him.</p></div><div class="stack stack--col stack__item-no-shrink | stack--spacing1 | size05 right out02 wide-md"><img class="" alt="" width="2000" height="3000" loading="lazy" js-autosizes src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-babies-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1200&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=91cce2a6c586f5e8081a514d3153f8ee" srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-babies-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=600&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=5130e2c801b32ef5dae0eb8e8c76069f 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20231104-mayron-pe-4-babies-FINAL.JPG?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1200&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&